41 §1280.21. Presidential preference primary election
42 A. A statewide presidential preference primary election shall be held on the
43 last Saturday in March in 2024 and every fourth year thereafter for the purpose of
44 allowing the electors voters of each political party in the state which has forty
45 thousand or more registered members to express their preference for a person to be
46 the nominee of the party for president of the United States.
